L2_gloss: The first letter of the Nganasan alphabet, written in the Cyrillic script.
polynya, place at sea where the water hasn't frozen
body of water that does not freeze in winter (a sea or lake)
to remain awake, to stay up
to throw, to chuck, to hurl
to begin to be on guard, to begin to worry, to look over one's shoulder
to become on guard, to begin to worry, to become roused
to sketch out, to draw the contours of
to stomp, to stamp one's foot
to say, to tell, to convey a message
to slacken (of a rope or wire)
to evaluate, determine the value of
